The paper deals with optimization problems and algorithms, which are typically studied in computer science. The focus is on Pareto fronts, which are commonly used in multi-objective optimization, suggesting cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as likely categories. The use of dynamic programming algorithms and complexity analysis suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as another likely category. The study of geometric properties of the Pareto front and the use of computational geometry techniques suggest cs.CG (Computational Geometry) as a possible category. Finally, the study of optimization problems and algorithms in general suggests cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as a possible category.
